This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Barack Obama in 2015. The memorandum addresses the use of Unmanned Aircraft Systems (UAS), commonly known as drones, in the United States. It acknowledges the rapid advancements in UAS technology and the potential benefits they can bring to various industries and government operations. However, it emphasizes the importance of safeguarding privacy, civil rights, and civil liberties while integrating UAS into the National Airspace System (NAS). The memorandum outlines policies and procedures that federal agencies must follow when using UAS, including privacy protections, civil rights and civil liberties protections, accountability measures, and transparency requirements. It also establishes a multi-stakeholder engagement process to develop best practices for commercial and private UAS use. The memorandum concludes with definitions and general provisions.